                              <td valign="top" style="font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color:#333333; font-size:12px; text-align:justify;">One more year is gone by... New Year is stock taking time.  What would you remember 2012 for? How many new friends? How many milestones  reached? How much better health? How much wealthier?  How better prepared are we? How closer have  we gone towards our goals?<br />

                                <br />                                <img src="{!URLFOR($Resource.NewsLetterImages,'NewsLetterImages/pic01.gif')}" width="250" height="300" align="left" />I was recently reading this book “The Leader Who Had No  Title” – by Robin Sharma. It gave me a new realisation, or should I call it a  revelation. That realisation was – A month of 30 days comes and goes before we  realise it. And we in all probability get to live only 960 of such months. <br />

                                    <br />

                                We  actually get on this earth just about 960 months to live, and that is if we are  lucky enough. Of which more than 300 – 350 of them are gone already.. We might  probably get another 250 odd months of good health and that is it.<br />

                                <br />

                                For some reason, this realisation seeded a sense of urgency  in my mind. There is not forever time to do things we want to do in this  lifetime. Too much to do, but too little time and where is the time to  procrastinate? <br />

                                <br />

                                I am one year older, my children are one year older, my  goals are one year closer.  Can I say  with confidence that I am better prepared now than I was last year for my future,  for my childrens’ future? <br />

                                <br />

                                I have moved ahead  though not as much as I would have liked to. I wasted my time and resources on  things that were not so important last year. I have to run faster from now on  and I am older.  <br />

                                <br />

                                Can I sit here and crib about it? I will be a one more year  older next year and I am at least fit and capable of working, earning, running,  saving, investing and doing whatever it takes...now. I don’t want to crib about  running even faster next year.<br />

                                <br />

                                So, I know what I want to do in 2013. I won’t call them New  Year resolutions. There was review, and now there is an action plan. I have  choices – I can follow my action plan and grow up while I grow older or I can  ignore it and grow just older but no better. I pray for strength to make the  right choice and stick to them. I would include you in my prayers too...<br />

                                <br />

